# Azure Container Registry (ACR) Integration with GitHub Codespaces

## Overview

This document provides a comprehensive guide to integrating **Azure Container Registry (ACR)** with **GitHub Codespaces** to ensure consistent package versions and dependencies across all development, staging, and production environments.

---

## Problem Statement

### Current Challenges Without ACR Integration

**Environment Inconsistency:**
- Developers use different package versions locally
- "Works on my machine" but fails in CI/CD
- Staging and production have different dependencies
- Docker images built in different environments produce different results

**Package Management Issues:**
- npm/pip versions drift over time
- No central source of truth for dependencies
- Hard to reproduce exact environment
- Manual synchronization error-prone

**Security & Compliance:**
- No audit trail of package versions used
- No centralized scanning for vulnerabilities
- No enforcement of approved package versions
- Compliance requirements not met

**Time Wasted:**
- Debugging environment-specific issues
- Rebuilding dependencies multiple times
- Manual Docker image creation
- Version compatibility troubleshooting

---

## Solution: Azure Container Registry (ACR)

### What is ACR?

Azure Container Registry is a managed, private Docker registry service that allows you to:
- ✅ Store Docker images in Azure (encrypted, secure)
- ✅ Manage image versions and tags
- ✅ Scan images for vulnerabilities
- ✅ Control access via Azure RBAC
- ✅ Integrate with CI/CD pipelines
- ✅ Serve as single source of truth for environments

### Architecture

```
Git Repository
    ↓ (Commit)
GitHub Actions / CI/CD Pipeline
    ↓ (Build Docker Image)
Azure Container Registry
    ↓ (Store Image)
├─ cimp-api:v1.2.3
├─ cimp-api:latest
├─ cimp-blazor:v1.2.3
├─ cimp-blazor:latest
├─ cimp-db-migrate:v1.2.3
└─ cimp-dev:latest
    ↓ (Pull Image)
GitHub Codespaces
├─ cimp-api (exact versions)
├─ cimp-blazor (exact versions)
└─ All dependencies locked
    ↓ (Pull Image)
Staging Environment
├─ cimp-api (exact versions)
├─ cimp-blazor (exact versions)
└─ All dependencies locked
    ↓ (Pull Image)
Production Environment
├─ cimp-api (exact versions)
├─ cimp-blazor (exact versions)
└─ All dependencies locked
```

