## Version Management Best Practices

### Tagging Strategy

Use semantic versioning with git tags:

```bash
# Create a release
git tag -a v1.2.3 -m "Release version 1.2.3"
git push origin v1.2.3

# GitHub Actions automatically:
# 1. Builds image
# 2. Tags with v1.2.3
# 3. Tags with 'latest'
# 4. Pushes to ACR
```

### Lock File Approach

Create `versions.lock.yml`:

```yaml
# versions.lock.yml
images:
  api:
    repository: cimpregistry.azurecr.io/cimp-api
    tag: v1.2.3
    digest: sha256:abc123...
    scanned: true
    vulnerabilities: 0
  
  blazor:
    repository: cimpregistry.azurecr.io/cimp-blazor
    tag: v1.2.3
    digest: sha256:def456...
    scanned: true
    vulnerabilities: 0
  
  postgres:
    repository: cimpregistry.azurecr.io/cimp-postgres
    tag: "15.2"
    digest: sha256:ghi789...
    scanned: true
    vulnerabilities: 0

dependencies:
  dotnet: 7.0.0
  node: 18.16.0
  npm: 9.6.7

generated: 2024-04-20T10:30:00Z
```

